draw((14,5)--(14,2));
draw((14,2)--(11,2));
label("A",(3.5,3.5));
label("B",(12.5,3.5));
[/asy] The final Answer is 12
 ### Proof
 Since square $A$ has a perimeter of 24 cm and all its sides are equal in length, each side measures $24/4=6$ cm. The area of square $A$ is thus $6\cdot6=36$ square cm.
 Thus, the area of square $B$ is $36/4=9$ square cm.
 So each side of square $B$ measures $\sqrt{9}=3$ cm. Finally, the perimeter of square $B$ is $4\cdot3=\boxed{12}$ cm.
 *)

